value.value: Life-threatening consequences; urgent operative intervention indicated

A rare non-Hodgkin lymphoma that arises from the liver and the bulk of the tumor is located in the liver.  The most frequent types of non-Hodgkin lymphoma that arise from the liver are diffuse large B-cell lymphoma and mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue lymphoma.

value.value: A rare mucosa-associated lymphoid tissue lymphoma that arises from the liver.  It is characterized by the presence of centrocyte-like cells surrounding germinal centers.  Lymphoepithelial lesions involving the bile duct epithelium may also be present.

Stage I Extrahepatic Bile Duct Cancer

value.value: Stage I includes: IA: (T1, N0, M0); IB: (T2, N0, M0).  T1: Tumor confined to the bile duct histologically.  T2: Tumor invades beyond the wall of the bile duct.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 6th ed.)
